edu.rit.gpu.example

Interface KnapsackProblem

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    KnapsackSC, SubsetSum

    public interface KnapsackProblem
    Interface KnapsackProblem is the interface for an object that defines a knapsack problem. The definition consists of the knapsack capacity, the number of items, and the weight and value of each item.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      long capacity()
      Get the knapsack capacity.
      int itemCount()
      Get the number of items, N.
      WV next()
      Get the weight and value of the next item.

      • next

        WV next()
        Get the weight and value of the next item. This method must be called N times to get all the items. Each method call returns a new WV object.
        Returns:
        Weight/value.
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if this method is called more than N times.
